<item>
            <title>[LU-819] &quot;lfs getstripe -M&quot; broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-819</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just testing sanity.sh test_56, and wanted to see whether &quot;lfs getstripe -M&quot; is working correctly.  However, it doesn&apos;t do what I would expect:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs getstripe -v /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56g/f56s.0
/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56g/f56s.0
lmm_magic:          0x0BD10BD0
lmm_seq:            0x200002b10
lmm_object_id:      0x1b4
lmm_stripe_count:   1
lmm_stripe_size:    1048576
lmm_stripe_pattern: 1
lmm_stripe_offset:  1
        obdidx           objid          objid            group
             1           10567         0x2947                0

# lfs getstripe -M /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56g/f56s.0
/mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56g/f56s.0 MDT index: 53
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I definitely do not have 54 MDTs in my filesystem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Secondly, the output format is very difficult to parse.  I would expect that the MDT index is printed as part of the &quot;lfs getstripe -v&quot; output, or possibly in addition to the normal &quot;-v&quot; output if &quot;-v -M&quot; is used?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In contrast, &quot;lfs getstripe -c&quot; prints just the requested stripe count:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# lfs getstripe -c /mnt/lustre/d0.sanity/d56g/f56s.0
1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
